\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_H::1><$Scr_Ps::0>
\f1\b\fs36 Applying Default Formatting to Existing Documents\
\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_H::1><!$Scr_Ps::0>
\f1\fs28 Setting the default formatting in the Preferences or Project Settings has no effect on existing documents. (Scrivener could ruin special formatting you have applied if it changed the formatting for all your documents automatically every time you changed the preferences.) To apply the default formatting to existing documents:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}In the binder, select the documents you want to update.\
{\listtext	2.	}From the main menu, select 
\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f2\b Documents > Convert > Text to Default Formatting\'85
\f0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f1\fs28 \
{\listtext	3.	}Check the options in the panel that appears and then click \'93OK\'94.\
}